President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the Commonwealth of Massachusetts and has ordered Federal assistance to support recovery efforts for areas affected by the COVID-19 pandemic. This includes Federal funding for Crisis Counseling and emergency protective measures. W. Russell Webster has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further assessments may lead to additional designations in the future. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.